  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">George Thompson writes: &quot;It is now the 4th of March the day of your President&apos;s [Franklin Pierce&apos;s] inauguration--it is the afternoon.&quot; Thompson describes his family. He has accepted invitations to lecture on American slavery. He comments on William Goodell&apos;s books on slavery. He discusses the British attitude toward the American slave question, and the influence of [Harriet Beecher] Stowe.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes envelope, with the delivery address: &quot;Miss Anne Warren Weston, Weymouth, Near Boston, (Mass.), United States.&quot; It is postmarked 4 March 1853.</subfield>
